attachments.title: The 3 Business Models That Matter for Connected Hardware Startups
attachments.text: Hardware has <http://changed.It|changed.It> used to be that a “hardware business” sold widgets made in China at a 30% gross margin. These widgets were protected with patents, manufactured by the millions, and replaced by new and better widgets 18 months later. Inevitably, a bigger company with deeper pockets, stronger manufacturing relationships, and better execution would come along with a slightly better widget at a lower price and make more money.
